  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3356404917" />
    <a title="Sophia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/115833656-sophia"><img alt="Sophia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1590492140p2/115833656.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3356404917?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sophia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sophia" href="/user/show/115833656-sophia">Sophia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3356404917" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer942065266928712323">&quot; Serenade &quot; is my recently finished book , Now having a new book on my lap i felt the need of saying a special farewell to this one :)<br/>Goodbyes hurt when the story is not finished in your heart but the book has been closed 💛<br/>No matter what I read after this , my heart will ache like the first day for Maximilian and Nadia&apos;s tragic &amp; historical Love Story ( i hate the ignorant love that is being shaped in ur heads as u read this , cause this one is a kind of commitment that only happens in beautifu</span>
  <span id="freeText942065266928712323" style="display:none">" Serenade " is my recently finished book , Now having a new book on my lap i felt the need of saying a special farewell to this one :)<br />Goodbyes hurt when the story is not finished in your heart but the book has been closed 💛<br />No matter what I read after this , my heart will ache like the first day for Maximilian and Nadia's tragic &amp; historical Love Story ( i hate the ignorant love that is being shaped in ur heads as u read this , cause this one is a kind of commitment that only happens in beautifully written books) <br />for Maya's warrior like soul and stubbornness, for that half-finished serenade i will never be able to hear but i know the musical , soul-wrecking pain :)<br />And lastly for the Great War that was merciless :)<br /><br /> You are and always will be my only recommendation to people who live more than one life ...<br /><br />Another thing i wanted to mention is : <br /><br />When you look around yourself or search within yourself through a litrosophical point of view , by finding beauties , stunning details and uniqueness of each creature , you realize the capability of the creator.<br />When i was reading this book , seeing how it was beautifully written in many fields ( art , history , romance, policts and...) i was amazed by Zülfü Livaneli 's knowledge , his unique expressions that will hunt me in my daily life and scenes he pictured in my head so well that now i feel it as a part of my memory rather than a line in book :)<br /><br />For instance: [ kendimi suyun koruyucu şevkatine bıraktım] will be with me everytime i bury myself into water with burdensome tiredness on my shoulders to find a bit of relief as the day come into an end like maya :)<br /><br />( i must say i read it in its original language - Turkish - and i believe whoever found a flaw in the way of writing is because the naivety of this language can hardly be translated the way it is )<br /><br />* Don't forget to highlight the best parts , its bittersweet when you look back and read them all after eveything is finished ...<br /><br />" I pressed the cold cover to my chest but it was the memories that warmed my heart inside " <br /><br />Thank you @zlivaneli 🌼</span>
  <a data-text-id="942065266928712323" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

